---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import KusadasiInfo from '~/components/widgets/AroundInfoFeatures.astro';
import Hero from '~/components/widgets/Hero.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '~/components/widgets/breadcrumb.astro';
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { ViewTransitions } from 'astro:transitions';
import photo from 'src/assets/images/sirince.jpg';
import BrakePad from 'astro-vtbot/components/BrakePad.astro';
import ProgressBar from 'astro-vtbot/components/ProgressBar.astro';



const metadata = {
  title: 'Sirince',
};
---
<ProgressBar />
{/* To observe the effect in DEV mode it is necessary to simulate 2000ms loading time */}
<BrakePad duration={2000} />

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <ViewTransitions />
  <!-- Hero Widget ******************* -->

  <Hero
    tagline=""
    title="Sirince Village"
    subtitle="Sirince: A Tranquil Retreat in Turkey's Aegean Region"
    image={{
      src: photo,
      alt: 'Sirince, Izmir',
    }}
  />

  <!-- Features2 Widget ************** -->
  <section class="px-4 md:px-6 py-2 sm:py-2 lg:py-2 mx-auto max-w-4xl">

<p class="text-base">


</p> 



<br>

<p class="text-base">
    Nestled in the verdant hills of the Aegean region, Sirince village stands 
    as a charming retreat near the bustling cities of Izmir and Kusadasi in Turkey.
     This picturesque village, with its cobblestone streets and traditional Ottoman houses,
      exudes an old-world charm that transports visitors back in time. Surrounded by
       vineyards and orchards, Sirince offers a serene atmosphere where travelers can 
       unwind and immerse themselves in the beauty of nature.
</p> <br>
<p class="text-base">  
    Sirince is renowned for its local wines and olive oils, which are produced using traditional 
    methods passed down through generations. Visitors can explore the village's 
    boutique wineries and olive oil presses, where they can sample the region's finest offerings
     and learn about the rich agricultural heritage of the area. Additionally,
     Sirince boasts a vibrant market scene, where artisans sell handcrafted goods such as pottery,
     textiles, and jewelry, making it the perfect destination for those seeking unique souvenirs
      to take home.
</p> <br>  

<div class="aspect-w-16 aspect-h-9">
    <iframe width="100%" height="480"  src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/BYZwnb1jRhg?si=FA6W2iV6v2dW9e0X" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>
    </div>


<p class="text-base">
    Beyond its culinary delights and artisanal offerings, Sirince is also steeped in history 
    and culture. The village is home to several well-preserved Byzantine-era churches, including
     the Church of St. John the Baptist, which dates back to the 6th century. Travelers 
     can explore these ancient landmarks and gain insight into the region's fascinating 
     past while marveling at the intricate frescoes and architectural details that adorn 
     these historic sites. With its blend of natural beauty, culinary delights, and cultural heritage,
      Sirince village offers a truly immersive experience for visitors seeking to 
      discover the authentic charm of Turkey's Aegean region.
</p> <br>




    </section>


    <KusadasiInfo />
  
  <!-- Breadcrumb -->


  <Breadcrumb firstText="Around Kusadasi" firstLink="/misc" title={metadata.title} />

</Layout>
